            <h2 class="blog-post-title">Motivation</h2>

            <p>
            	There are many sites on the internet that display crime data for a particular region. However, most of these sites incorporate a massive amount of data that can be overwhelming for ordinary individuals to analaze and draw conculsions.
            </p>

            <blockquote>
              <p>Our <strong>GOAL</strong> is to visually display the <strong> TOP 10 </strong> occuring crimes for a particular region of San Diego.</p>
            </blockquote>

            <p>
            	The DELPHI crime data is relevant to the San Diego community and would be very helpful for a broad range of people from researchers to potential home buyers. Our motivation for this project is to make the visualization of the data as simple and user friendly with interactive graphs instead of just raw data.
            </p>

            <h3>Data</h3>
            <p>
            	Our data is from Delphi. We are using the “San Diego Regional Crimes” data set.
            	The table we are accessing is called "arjis_crimes". The table consists of the following columns:

            </p>
            <ul>

              <li>agency <em>(Police/Sheriff)</em></li>
              <li>charge_description <em>(Name of the crime)</em></li>
              <li>activity_date <em>(Year-Month-Day Hour:Min:Sec)</em></li>
              <li>block_address <em>(Address)</em></li>
              <li>zip <em>(Zip Code)</em></li>
              <li>community <em>(City)</em></li>

            </ul>

            <h2>Word Cloud</h2>

            <p>
            	The main visualization of Siete is a <strong> word cloud </strong>. The word cloud displays the most common occurring crimes for a particular zip code. The size rendering of the crime in the word cloud is determined by the number of times that crime occurs in the database table. 
            </p>

            <h3>Example Query for Word Cloud</h3>

            <p>
            	The query below selects the top 30 crimes for a particular zipcode.
            </p>

            <pre>
            	<code>
            		SELECT "charge_description", COUNT(*) 
            		FROM "arjis_crimes"
            		WHERE "zip"='92026'
            		GROUP BY "charge_description"
            		ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC 
            		LIMIT 30
            	</code>
            </pre>

            <p>
            	With a word cloud, you are able to visualize the types of crimes that occur and their relative frequencies for a particular region. The word cloud is visually appealing because of its incorporation of different font colors and sizes.
            </p>

